Excise officials arrested a 47-year-old woman near Peroorkada on Saturday for alleged possession of 60 grams of ganja.According to S. Vinod Kumar, Circle Inspector, Excise (Thiruvananthapuram Circle), the accused has been identified as Usha, from Puthuvalputhenveedu, Adupu Koottan Para, near Peroorkada.She was nabbed during a raid that was conducted in her house.The accused was charged under Section (b)(ii)(A) [pertaining to producing, possessing, selling, purchasing, transporting or using cannabis in small quantities] of the Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Act, 1985.Incidentally, the accused personâ€™s husband was serving a jail term under recently in connection with the narcotic drug case.The accused was produced before the Judicial First Class Magistrate Court.The Excise team included Preventive officer Sunil Kumar, Civil Excise officers Tony, Rejina and Sudheesh.